        <exercisegroup cols="2">
            <exercise>
                <statement>
                    <p>Count the number of terms in the expression.<ol label="a." cols="2">
                        <li><p><m>5x+10y-3z</m></p></li>
                        <li><p><m>-2t+s</m></p></li>
                        <li><p><m>2x</m></p></li>
                        <li><p><m>9x-2z-4x+z</m></p></li>
                    </ol></p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <p><ol label="a." cols="2">
                        <li><p>This expression has <m>3</m> terms.</p></li>
                        <li><p>This expression has <m>2</m> terms.</p></li>
                        <li><p>This expression has <m>1</m> term.</p></li>
                        <li><p>This expression has <m>4</m> terms.</p></li>
                    </ol></p>
                </solution>
            </exercise>
        </exercisegroup>

        <exercisegroup cols="2">
            <exercise>
                <statement>
                    <p>List the terms in the expression.<ol label="a." cols="2">
                        <li><p><m>-2x+4y</m>.</p></li>
                        <li><p><m>8x^2-20x^2+4x</m></p></li>
                        <li><p><m>5a-2b+6a-7b</m></p></li>
                        <li><p><m>x</m></p></li>
                    </ol></p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <p><ol label="a." cols="2">
                        <li><p>The terms are <m>-2x</m> and <m>4y</m>.</p></li>
                        <li><p>The terms are <m>8x^2</m>, <m>-20x^2</m>, and <m>4x</m>.</p></li>
                        <li><p>The terms are <m>5a</m>, <m>-2b</m>, <m>6a</m>, and <m>-7b</m>.</p></li>
                        <li><p>The term is <m>x</m>.</p></li>
                    </ol></p>
                </solution>
            </exercise>
        </exercisegroup>

        <exercisegroup cols="2">
            <exercise>
                <statement>
                    <p>Where possible, simplify the following expressions by combining like terms.<ol label="a." cols="2">
                        <li><p><m>6c+12c-5c</m></p></li>
                        <li><p><m>-5q^2-3q^2</m></p></li>
                        <li><p><m>-3x-5y+4.5x</m></p></li>
                        <li><p><m>2x-3y+4z</m></p></li>
                    </ol></p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <p><ol label="a.">
                        <li><p>All three terms are like terms, so they may combined. We combine them two at a time:<md>
                            <mrow>6c+12c-5c \amp=18c-5c</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp=13c</mrow>
                        </md></p></li>
                        <li><p>The two terms <m>-5q^2</m> and <m>-3q^2</m> are like terms, so we may combine them:<md>
                            <mrow>-5q^2-3q^2 \amp=-8q^2</mrow>
                        </md></p></li>
                        <li><p>The two terms <m>-3x</m> and <m>4.5x</m> are like terms so we can combine them, while the other term is different.<md>
                            <mrow>-3x-5y+4.5x</mrow>
                            <mrow>\amp=1.5x-5y</mrow>
                        </md></p></li>
                        <li><p>The expression <m>2x-3y+4z</m> cannot be simplified as there are no like terms.</p></li>
                    </ol></p>
                </solution>
            </exercise>
        </exercisegroup>

    </exercises>

